Your Honor,

I stand before you today as Robert Chapman, pleading guilty to the offense of speeding. I accept full responsibility for my actions and understand the consequences of my behavior. 

I deeply regret the danger I posed to those around me by engaging in excessive speed. I acknowledge that my curiosity about the capabilities of my new car clouded my judgment, which led me to commit this offense. However, it is important to note that my intention was never to harm anyone. 

At the age of 26, I am aware that my actions were irresponsible and that I should have known better. I understand that I have accumulated penalty points from previous speeding incidents, which demonstrates a pattern of reckless behavior. However, I want to emphasize that apart from these driving offenses, I have maintained a clean record.

In addition, I have recently been diagnosed with ADHD, which may have contributed to impulsive decision-making and difficulty focusing on important matters, such as checking my mail. This condition does not excuse my actions, but it provides an insight into the underlying challenges I face.

I assure you, Your Honor, that I have taken this incident as a wake-up call. I have begun seeking professional help and exploring strategies to manage my ADHD. I am committed to making the necessary changes to prevent any future offenses. 

I am fully aware of the need to compensate for the harm caused by my speeding. While I understand that I cannot undo the past, I am willing to undertake any actions necessary to contribute positively to society and prevent the recurrence of similar offenses. 

Your Honor, I want you to know that I have reflected deeply on the impact of my actions. I have experienced genuine remorse and have learned from this experience. I am committed to becoming a responsible and law-abiding citizen.

In conclusion, I plead guilty to the offense of speeding and accept the associated consequences. I respectfully ask for your leniency, taking into account my young age, lack of criminal record, and my genuine efforts to address the underlying issues that contributed to this offense.

Thank you for your attention.

